criteria.textblock:
        The inclusion criteria are:

          -  Aged 65-89;

          -  Possible sarcopenia (defined by AWGS 2019);

          -  No cognitive impairment (Abbreviated Mental Test score ≥8); and

          -  No communication problems.

        The exclusion criteria are:

          -  having engaged in a structured exercise programme in the past 6 months or planning to
             do so within the intervention period;

          -  mobility-limiting injury of the hands or lower limbs, surgery or hospitalisation
             within the intervention period;

          -  contraindications such as musculoskeletal/cardiorespiratory disorders, or any advanced
             diseases that inhibit them from exercising.
